long_desc.thetext:
Your package grass failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17719299
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild

Is this the error?
DEBUG util.py:435: Error: nothing provides libgfortran.so.3()(64bit) needed by openblas-openmp-0.2.19-4.fc26.ppc64le. DEBUG util.py:435: nothing provides libgfortran.so.3()(64bit) needed by openblas-openmp-0.2.19-4.fc26.ppc64le
Yes, but that's no longer an issue. I'll kick off a scratch build to see if there are other issues.
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.

The ctypes compilation issue was caused by new declarations introduced by GCC 7 which is used in F26. Tracked and fixed upstream in https://trac.osgeo.org/grass/ticket/3331#comment:46
I attach here the needed small patch for 7.0.5 (i.e., https://trac.osgeo.org/grass/changeset/71223).
Created attachment 1292001 Patch to fix ctypes compilation issue on F26/gcc7

attachment.desc: Patch to fix ctypes compilation issue on F26/gcc7
